-- U.K. 10-Year Gilts Decline With Yield Increasing to 2.45 Percent
-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 2012-03-21T08:40:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/u-k-10-year-gilts-decline-with-yield-increasing-to-2-45-percent.html
U.K. 10-year gilts declined for the
first time in three days, with the yield rising two basis
points, or 0.02 percentage point, to 2.45 percent at 8:36 a.m.
London time.  The pound advanced against the dollar, trading 0.4 percent
higher at $1.5918. Sterling was little changed at 83.43 pence
per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in Edinburgh at 
